Butterscotch, golden-brown. The color of the Martian sky.

Head. The uppermost part of the human body, containing the brain and face.
An asset or resource, wealth. A useful or otherwise desirable thing, or access to such things.

To love. To have a passionate affection for (someone).
Saddle. A cut of meat from the back of an animal, between the shoulders and the loin.
Expensive. To cost a large amount of money, or to be rare or scarce but sought after.
Foot. The bottommost part of the human body, or an analogous part on an animal or a machine, used for walking.
Public. Communal or open to use by anyone. (of a service or resource) provided for free to citizens of a community or region.
Park. A planned natural area or public garden within an urban settlement.

Sea. A large body of salt water, esp. one that is landlocked.

Additionally, furthermore. Used at the beginning of a sentence to expand on what has already been said.
